# No Deleting Documentation

Do not delete documentation files as part of routine cleanup, refactors, or “tidying.” This includes everything under `docs/`, especially `docs/handoffs/`.

- Do not remove handoff or feature docs because a task is “done” or superseded — they are historical context for humans and future sessions.
- If content is wrong or obsolete, prefer updating the doc with a short note or superseding section rather than deleting the file.
- Only remove a doc when the user explicitly asks to delete that specific file (or clearly authorizes removal of named paths).
